[
  "Luis Enrique Yarur Rey is the chairman of Banco de Credito e Inversiones (BCI), a Chilean retail and commercial bank.",
  "BCI has more than 300 branches throughout Chile and Florida, and even one in Antarctica. ",
  "The bank was founded by the Yarur family in 1937. Today it is one of Chile's largest banking institutions, with more than $45 billion in assets. ",
  "In 2015, BCI purchased City National Bank of Florida for $947 million; it was the first time a Chilean bank purchased a U.S. financial institution. "
]